post.title: Are you tired of politics and the politicization of everything?

body: Yes very much so. Going out to eat shouldn't be political. Going to school shouldn't be political. We sure as hell shouldn't be foaming at the mouth when people do those things with/without a mask. I didn't want to be within 6' of your ass in 2018, COVID didn't change that.

post.title: Are you tired of politics and the politicization of everything?

body: I don't think so. Biden will immediately begin to dismantle things Trump has done on immigration and taxes, he'll get at least one supreme court pick probably right off the bat, I believe Ruth is holding on in the hopes Trump loses and she can step down, he'll probably try and start programs most conservatives and lots of moderates don't like, such as red flag laws and gun control, we're in for a continued shit-storm for years to come because of how vitriolic the sides are now. On top of that will be years of investigations, biased and un-biased, into President Trump, his family and his cabinet by the House, maybe Senate, and probably Southern District for New York.

post.title: Are you tired of politics and the politicization of everything?

body: I sure am. I also can't stand how there seems to be no room for nuance. It is frustrating how certain stances on issues become the "property" of a political side. For example, just because I support free market capitalism and the 2nd Amendment, shouldn't mean that I can't support vaccines (which I strongly do) or exploring alternative energy sources (so long as it doesn't become a government cash-grab). I believe that we have to be open to getting the "best of ALL worlds", rather than wholly chaining ourselves to one of two political parties.

For example, just because I support free market capitalism and the 2nd Amendment, shouldn't mean that I can't support vaccines (which I strongly do) or exploring alternative energy sources (so long as it doesn't become a government cash-grab). I believe that we have to be open to getting the "best of ALL worlds", rather than wholly chaining ourselves to one of two political parties.
